# Trivy misconfiguration ignores. Each entry must document WHY the rule
# does not apply. Keep this list short and justified.

# DS-0002 "Specify a non-root USER".
# src/claude-agents/Dockerfile.base is the base image for a
# per-session VM, not a shared-kernel container. The
# isolation boundary is the VM itself; the agent runner and user
# workloads legitimately need root for runtime `apt install` and native
# builds. A USER directive would break those without adding isolation the
# VM doesn't already provide.
AVD-DS-0002
